Preamble
This license governs the use, modification, distribution, and publication of the
software and documentation contained in the Golden Times · Stor · History · Publisher
repository. It is intentionally concise, practical, and tailored to the project's
goals: open distribution, clear attribution, and release-bound licensing traceability.

Definitions
- "Software" means the source code, documentation, assets, scripts, styles,
  configuration files, and other materials contained in this repository.
- "Release" means a versioned publication of the Software associated with a
  Git tag (e.g., v0.1.0) and the corresponding GitHub Release entry.
- "You" means any person or entity that obtains a copy of the Software.

Grant of Rights
1. Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy
   of the Software and associated documentation files (the "Software"), to use,
   copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell copies of
   the Software, subject to the conditions below.

Conditions
2. Attribution
   - Redistributions of source code or binaries must retain the above copyright
     notice, this permission notice, and a reference to the originating repository:
     https://github.com/RFOF/Golden-Times-stor-history-Publisher
   - When publishing a packaged release derived from this Software, include a
     clear reference to the original repository and the Release tag or commit SHA
     that served as the basis for the published package.

3. Release Traceability
   - Any public redistribution that is presented as a "release" or "package"
     must include the Release tag (e.g., v0.1.0) and the `release-log.json` or
     equivalent metadata that documents the commit SHA and license hash at the
     time of release. This ensures reproducibility and legal traceability.

4. No External Dependencies Mandate
   - Distributions that claim compatibility with the Golden Times project must
     not require external, proprietary, or third-party services for core
     functionality unless explicitly documented and consented by RFOF-NETWORK.
     (This clause preserves the project's principle of self-contained operation.)

5. No Trademark Grant
